Here's the full **testsmells.org 19-smell academic catalog** audit of `UserRepositoryIntegrationTests.cs`, with integration-test calibration applied.

---

## Summary Dashboard

```
┌──────────┬─────────────┬────────────────┐
│ Severity │ Smell Count │ Affected Tests │
├──────────┼─────────────┼────────────────┤
│ High     │ 3           │ 3              │
│ Medium   │ 1           │ 1              │
│ Low      │ 0           │ 0              │
├──────────┼─────────────┼────────────────┤
│ Total    │ 4           │ 4              │
└──────────┴─────────────┴────────────────┘
```

**4 of 8 tests are clean.** The well-structured tests (`InsertUser_PersistsToDatabase` aside from Assertion Roulette, `UpdateUser_ModifiesExistingRecord`, `DeleteUser_RemovesFromDatabase`, `ListUsers_ReturnsAllInserted`) follow good patterns: clear naming, focused scope, proper assertions, and proper use of in-memory SQLite (avoiding a real Mystery Guest).

---

## Findings by Severity

### 🔴 HIGH — Sleepy Test

**Smell:** Sleepy Test (Smell #3)
**Test:** `NotifyOnInsert_SendsEventAfterDelay` (line 87)
**Calibration:** Even for integration tests, `Thread.Sleep` is a smell — it introduces non-determinism and slows the suite.

```csharp
// ❌ Current — hard-coded 3-second sleep
Thread.Sleep(3000);
Assert.IsTrue(_repository.WasNotificationSent(user.Id));
```

```csharp
// ✅ Fix — poll with a timeout
var timeout = TimeSpan.FromSeconds(5);
var sw = Stopwatch.StartNew();
while (sw.Elapsed < timeout)
{
    if (_repository.WasNotificationSent(user.Id))
        break;
    await Task.Delay(50);
}
Assert.IsTrue(_repository.WasNotificationSent(user.Id),
    "Notification was not sent within the timeout period.");
```

**Risk if unfixed:** Flaky failures on slower CI agents; 3s overhead added to every suite run.

---

### 🔴 HIGH — Conditional Test Logic

**Smell:** Conditional Test Logic (Smell #1)
**Test:** `GetUser_ReturnsCorrectType` (lines 101–108)

```csharp
// ❌ Current — if/else means one branch is never tested
if (loaded is PremiumUser premium)
{
    Assert.IsTrue(premium.DiscountRate > 0);
}
else
{
    Assert.AreEqual("Eve", loaded!.Name);
}
```

```csharp
// ✅ Fix — split into two deterministic tests
[TestMethod]
public void GetUser_StandardUser_ReturnsName()
{
    _repository.Insert(new User("eve@example.com", "Eve"));
    var loaded = _repository.GetByEmail("eve@example.com");

    Assert.IsNotNull(loaded);
    Assert.AreEqual("Eve", loaded.Name);
}

[TestMethod]
public void GetUser_PremiumUser_HasDiscountRate()
{
    _repository.Insert(new PremiumUser("eve@example.com", "Eve", discountRate: 0.1m));
    var loaded = _repository.GetByEmail("eve@example.com") as PremiumUser;

    Assert.IsNotNull(loaded);
    Assert.IsTrue(loaded.DiscountRate > 0);
}
```

**Risk if unfixed:** One branch silently never executes — hidden gap in test coverage. You can't tell from a green build which path ran.

---

### 🔴 HIGH — Assertion-Free Test (Unknown Test)

**Smell:** Unknown Test / Assertion-Free Test (Smell #4)
**Test:** `BulkInsert_RunsWithoutErrors` (lines 113–119)

```csharp
// ❌ Current — no assertion; passes even if Insert silently fails
[TestMethod]
public void BulkInsert_RunsWithoutErrors()
{
    for (int i = 0; i < 100; i++)
    {
        _repository.Insert(new User($"bulk{i}@example.com", $"Bulk User {i}"));
    }
}
```

The name implies a "does not throw" intent, but the framework already fails on unhandled exceptions — this test adds zero verification beyond what a bare method call provides.

```csharp
// ✅ Fix — assert the observable outcome
[TestMethod]
public void BulkInsert_PersistsAllRecords()
{
    for (int i = 0; i < 100; i++)
    {
        _repository.Insert(new User($"bulk{i}@example.com", $"Bulk User {i}"));
    }

    var users = _repository.ListAll();
    Assert.AreEqual(100, users.Count);
}
```

**Risk if unfixed:** False confidence — `Insert` could silently swallow errors and this test would still pass.

---

### 🟡 MEDIUM — Assertion Roulette

**Smell:** Assertion Roulette (Extended Catalog)
**Test:** `InsertUser_PersistsToDatabase` (lines 35–38)

```csharp
// ❌ Current — 4 assertions, no messages; failure output is ambiguous
Assert.IsNotNull(loaded);
Assert.AreEqual("Alice", loaded.Name);
Assert.AreEqual("alice@example.com", loaded.Email);
Assert.IsTrue(loaded.Id > 0);
```

```csharp
// ✅ Fix — add discriminating messages
Assert.IsNotNull(loaded, "User should be retrievable after insert.");
Assert.AreEqual("Alice", loaded.Name, "Name should round-trip through persistence.");
Assert.AreEqual("alice@example.com", loaded.Email, "Email should round-trip through persistence.");
Assert.IsTrue(loaded.Id > 0, "Id should be auto-assigned on insert.");
```

**Risk if unfixed:** When a failure occurs in CI, the developer must open the source to determine which property was wrong.

---

## Smells Scanned — No Findings (15 of 19 Clean)

| # | Smell | Status | Notes |
|---|-------|--------|-------|
| 2 | **Mystery Guest** | ✅ Clean | Uses in-memory SQLite — a proper test fake, not an external resource |
| 5 | **Eager Test** | ✅ Clean | Max 3 production methods per test; integration-test calibration downgrades further |
| 6 | **Magic Number Test** | ✅ Clean | `3` and `10` in count assertions are contextually self-documenting (items just added) |
| 7 | **Sensitive Equality** | ✅ Clean | No `.ToString()` in assertions |
| 8 | **Exception Handling** | ✅ Clean | No `try`/`catch` in test methods |
| 9 | **General Fixture** | ✅ Clean | Both `_connection` and `_repository` are used by all 8 tests |
| 10 | **Ignored Test** | ✅ Clean | No `[Ignore]` or skip attributes |
| 11 | **Duplicate Assert** | ✅ Clean | No duplicate assertion parameters |
| 12 | **Lazy Test** | ✅ Clean | Tests share helper methods but test distinct behaviors |
| 13 | **Constructor Init** | ✅ Clean | Properly uses `[TestInitialize]`, not a constructor |
| 14 | **Default Test** | ✅ Clean | Class name is descriptive, not auto-generated |
| 15 | **Redundant Print** | ✅ Clean | No `Console.WriteLine` or debug output |
| 16 | **Redundant Assertion** | ✅ Clean | No tautological assertions |
| 17 | **Resource Optimism** | ✅ Clean | In-memory DB — no external file/service assumptions |
| 18 | **Empty Test** | ✅ Clean | All methods contain executable statements |

---

## Prioritized Remediation Plan

| Priority | Smell | Test | Effort | Why First |
|----------|-------|------|--------|-----------|
| 1 | Assertion-Free Test | `BulkInsert_RunsWithoutErrors` | ~2 min | Prevents false-pass — test verifies nothing today |
| 2 | Conditional Test Logic | `GetUser_ReturnsCorrectType` | ~5 min | Eliminates hidden untested branch |
| 3 | Sleepy Test | `NotifyOnInsert_SendsEventAfterDelay` | ~5 min | Removes flakiness + 3s suite slowdown |
| 4 | Assertion Roulette | `InsertUser_PersistsToDatabase` | ~1 min | Add message strings for CI debuggability |

**Bottom line:** Half the test suite is well-designed. The four smells found are concentrated in distinct methods and can be fixed in under 15 minutes total. Priorities 1–2 are the most urgent because they mask gaps in coverage.
